            <title>[KAFKA-5414] Console consumer offset commit regression</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5414</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5327&quot; title=&quot;Console Consumer should only poll for up to max messages&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-5327&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-5327&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the behavior of console consumer was changed to only commit offsets when the process closes. Previously we used periodic offset commits. This breaks existing usage in system tests and probably elsewhere.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
